<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 16:00 GMT January 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Six people were killed and seven others injured
when a bus fell into a valley in India's Uttar Pradesh early
today, Press Trust of India (PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- The Tajik government and the Islamic opposition began
their two-week negotiations here today, focusing on creation of a
reconciliation commission and participation of the opposition
group in the government.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Differences still impeded the Palestinians and
Israelis from clinching a deal on Israeli troop pullout from the
West Bank town of Hebron, said the Minister of Local Government of
the Palestinian National Authority(PNA).
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France today denied an allegation by Zairean rebels
that 1,000 French troops are deployed in Kisangani, northeast
Zaire, to help Zaire government troops take back the territories
lost to the rebels.
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu has told
Hebron settlers that, on the day the Hebron agreement is signed,
they will be given permission to expand their community in the
city, the Jerusalem Post reported today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
