<HEADLINE> British PM to Pay Brief Visit to Netherlands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister John Major
will pay a brief visit to the Netherlands on Tuesday to discuss
issues concerning the European Union (EU) with Dutch government
leaders.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Xinhua this afternoon, a Downing
Street spokesman said that Dutch Prime Minister Wim Kok, whose
country is holding the rotating EU presidency, invited Major to
pay a private working visit to The Hague.
</P>
<P>
During talks over dinner, the two prime ministers will exchange
views on the "key issues" of the EU's Inter-Governmental
Conference and other matters of common interest, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Major is expected to return to London later in
the evening. 
</P>
