<HEADLINE> IRA Launches Rocket Attack in N. Ireland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Irish Republican Army (IRA)
admitted today it carried out a rocket attack on the high court in
Belfast, the capital of Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Security sources were quoted as saying that the blast was
caused by a primitive device launched at a joint army and police
checkpoint near the heavily protected buildings in the center of
the city.
</P>
<P>
A caller to a Belfast radio station said that bombs had also
been left at six locations in the city, including the main railway
station, according to a BBC report. 
