<HEADLINE> Iraq Hails UAE's Call to Lift Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Iraq today hailed the call by
President of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) Sheikh Zayed Bin
Sultan al-Nahyan for the lifting of the embargo imposed on it.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed Saeed al-Sahaf
said Iraq highly appreciates al-Nahyan's call which expresses a
"responsible Arab stance."
</P>
<P>
The UAE president made the call at the session of the Gulf
Cooperation Council Health Ministers yesterday, urging an end to
the embargo. He also asked Arabs to achieve reconciliation and
jointly meet challenges.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sahaf appealed to the Arab nations, especially the Gulf
states, to support al-Nahyan's positions which, he said are in
the interests of all the Arab states.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations has imposed sanctions on Iraq since the
end of the 1990-91 Gulf crisis following its invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
</TEXT>
