<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 330 Die of Meningitis in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A total of 330 people died of
meningitis in Cabo Delgado Province, northern Mozambique during
the period from early May to late December last year, the local
newspaper "Noticias" reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed yesterday by Manuel Novela, a doctor from
the northern province, who added that 3,095 meningitis patients
are still receiving treatment in hospitals.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that the province has a low capacity for
controlling this epidemic. The situation there is worrying
because of the worsening medical conditions, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
