<HEADLINE> Reduction of Interest Rates Called for in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambia Association of Chambers
of Commerce and Industry (ZACCI) has urged the Zambian government
to reduce interest rates to promote economic growth.
</P>
<P>
ZACCI Chairman George Chabwera also said the country's
agricultural policy must focus on food self-sufficiency and a
surplus for export.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail today quoted him as saying that in order to
promote economic growth, the government should first reduce its
borrowing by way of treasury bills and then broaden its tax base,
even if it means revising the poll tax, and cut public spending.
</P>
<P>
He said that many people feel frustrated at the poverty and
tragedies afflicting Africa in spite of the several billions of
Dollars poured on African economies since 1960s by donors.
</P>
<P>
"In fact, Africans in sub-Saharan Africa are poorer now than
in 1960s. This need not be the case in Zambia," said the
chairman.
</P>
<P>
"We must provide extension and marketing and introduce new
export for such crops as beans, cassava and rubber, which can
easily be grown by small-scale farmers," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also called for incentives to promote investment in
education to help parents to push their children to do well in
school. 
</P>
