<HEADLINE> Aidid Threatens to Punish Participants in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Faction leader Hussein
Mohamed Aidid today threatened that he will arrest all those who
attended the recent Sodare of Ethiopia meeting by 26 Somali
factions.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Hussein Aidid told reporters today that the
participants of Sodare meeting will be caught once they are seen
in the territories controlled by their government.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Mohamed Afrah, who is also the interior minister of
Hussein Aidid's self-styled government, said those found to have
attended the meeting will be charged for treason.
</P>
<P>
He characterized the meeting as a purely set up meant to
disintegrate Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The harsh words of Aidid are said to be affecting some of the
Sodare meeting participants who belong to the United Somali
Congress of Murusade clan whose base is in South Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The threat will also affect members from the minority
communities of the United Somali Roots and the Somali Salvation
Council factions.
</P>
<P>
The threat of Hussein Aidid came just three days after a
meeting by 26 Somali factions was concluded in Sodare of Ethiopia
where an 11-member National Salvation Council of Somalia was
formed.
</P>
<P>
Among the council are five co-chairmen including Osman Ali
Atto and Ali Mahdi Mohamed. 
