<HEADLINE> U.S.Donates 25 Jeeps to Peace-keepers in Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The United States donated 25
Toyota jeeps to the west African peace-keeping force in Liberia known
as ECOMOG, the News Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The jeeps were presented to the ECOMOG on Saturday by Herbert Betz,
the project manager of the Pacific Architect Engineers, on behalf of
the U.S. government.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a brief ceremony at the ECOMOG headquarters in
Monrovia, ECOMOG Commander, Victor Malu expressed his thanks to the
U.S. government for its goodwill gesture that will help enhance the
peace-keepers' operational capability in Liberia.
</P>
<P>
He reinterated the ECOMOG's determination to end Liberia's conflict
by June this year. 
</P>
