<HEADLINE> Dutch Construction Industry Turnover Up Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 6 (Xinhua) -- The Dutch construction
industry recorded an increase in turnover of three percent in
1996, in spite of a poor start due to the severe weather, it was
reported today by Statistics Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The figures published by the Dutch Government's statistical
office revealed that the production of homes and other buildings
increased by one percent and that of civil and marine engineering
projects and roads by three percent.
</P>
<P>
The number of companies in the sector employing permanent staff
also increased, going up two percent to over 30,000, the figures
showed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
