<HEADLINE> S. Africa Invests 2 Billion U.S. Dollars in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The companies, most of them in mining, financial services and
retail industries, operate in the southern African region, said
the research issued by the Policy Information and Research Group
based here.
</P>
<P>
The release of the survey came few months after the Central
Bank and Finance Ministry introduced steps to ease foreign
exchange restrictions on South African firms investing in
Southern African region.
</P>
<P>
Growth potential of the consumer and retail industries in
South Africa will depend on the performance of the African
economies, some of which were growing faster than the modest 3.0
rate of South Africa last year, said the survey.
</P>
<P>
Economic reforms in these countries appeared to have created
significant middle classes, a main power that bolstered the
consumer industries.
</P>
<P>
Financial services also advance into the African market
following mining and retailing companies and there are more and
more banks participating in doing business with South African
corporations.
</P>
<P>
The survey came after the South Africa has been committed to
the development of the Southern African Region and begun to
rewrite some original trade arrangements. 
