<HEADLINE> Development of Small, Medium Firms Urged in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe needs to formulate a
strategy to develop the small and medium scale sector if the
indigenisation of the economy is to succeed, the Zimbabwe
National Chamber of Commerce (ZNCC) said in a paper released
today.
</P>
<P>
The ZNCC said it realised that there is need for
sub-contracting to allow blacks to move into the mainstream
economy.
</P>
<P>
" A small scale industry strategy should be integrated within
the framework of the economy as a whole to ensure compatibility
between macro-economic and micro economic interventions,'' the
ZNCC said.
</P>
<P>
According to the ZNCC, sub-contracting could open avenues for
many struggling small and medium scale enterprise, create
employment and enable larger companies to do away with peripheral
services and improve their efficiency. 
</P>
