<HEADLINE> First Mideast Commerce Conference Starts in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The first Middle East
commerce and administration conference entitled "Globalization of
Arab Commerce" started here today.
</P>
<P>
Participants of the three-day meeting, organized by the
Kuwaiti Faculty and Royal Holloway College of London University,
are expected to discuss 13 studies.
</P>
<P>
Attending the conference are representatives of scientific
institutes in the United States, Britain, Holland, Sweden, Gulf
and Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Hamad Al-Ibrahim, Dean of the faculty of administrative
sciences of Kuwait University, said in a lecture after the
opening ceremony that the discussions would touch on future of
the business sector in the Arab world, particularly in Kuwait and
other Gulf states.
</P>
<P>
Head of the conference's organizing committee Ali Al-Shemali
said the meeting would discuss three studies, which deal with the
nature of Arab trade administration, ways of globalizing the
market and the introduction of data technology in commercial
strategies.
</P>
<P>
The second conference of this nature is expected to be held in
the United Arab Emirates or Saudi Arabia, a conference source
said. 
</P>
