<HEADLINE> Three Rebels Killed in Western Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Three members of an
anti-government organization of Iran were killed when they hit
mine fields in Iran's western province of Kermanshahan.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the two men and
one woman of the Iraq-based armed opposition group People's
Mojahedin of Iran (PMOI) were chased by regional tribal forces
while they were trying to cross the border line between Iran and
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the PMOI staged a series of bombing attacks around
the country during the fourth Iranian parliamentary
elections. The Tehran government reacted by staging an air raid
on PMOI base inside the Iraqi territory.
</P>
<P>
The PMOI, the largest anti-government organization was founded
in 1964 and declared outlawed by the government in 1981. The
opposition exiled force fought on Baghdad side in the 1980-88
Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
There are about 20,000 PMOI members residing in Iraq under the
leadership of Mass'oud Rajavi who lives in Iraq at the moment.
</P>
