<HEADLINE> Turkey Issues New 5-million Lira Banknotes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Central Bank today
began issuing the largest banknotes of 5 million Liras (about 45.7
U.S. dollars) to keep pace with a skyrocketing inflation.
</P>
<P>
The annual inflation rate has kept around 70 to 80 percent
for the past decade. And the government plans to bring it down to
60 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank put the previously largest 1 million lira
banknotes into circulation in January 1995.
</P>
<P>
Like all other Turkish paper money, the new banknotes feature
a portrait of Mustafa Kemal Ataturk, founder of the Turkish
Republic.
</P>
<P>
The latest banknote is the ninth issue since 1981, when the
1,000 lira banknote was the largest denomination. 
</P>
