<DOCNO> XIE19970107.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU More Than Self-sufficient in Wine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 28 billion litres of
wine will be available within the European Union (EU) during the
1996/97 marketing year, to satisfy an estimated average per capita
consumption of 34.57 litres by the Community's citizens.
</P>
<P>
These figures emerge from the official forward estimate for the
1996/97 wine year, published recently by the European Commission
(EC), the executive body of the EU.
</P>
<P>
Based on data forwarded by EU member states, the EC experts
reckon EU wine-grower will produce 176.18 million hectolitres (a
hectolitre (hl) is 100 litre) during the year.
</P>
<P>
Existing stocks of just over 110 million hl and exports of over
five million hl will swell the total wine availability to the
final estimate figure.
</P>
<P>
The Commission calculated that 127.37 million hl of these wines
would be consumed within the EU, making the Community "121 percent
self-sufficient" in wine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
