<HEADLINE> Industrial Products Top Vietnam Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's industrial exports in
1996 totaled four billion U.S. dollars, more than half of the
country's 7.1-billion-dollar overall export volume, the Trade
Ministry said here today.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's principal industrial export items -- oil and related
products -- made up to 1.2 billion dollars in 1996. They were
followed by garments and textiles which were worth 1.1 billion
dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Shoes and leather exports, the third largest export items,
totaled 500 million dollars while anthracite (black coal) and
heavy industrial mineral products amounted to 100 million dollars
and 50 million dollars respectively. 
