<HEADLINE> Building Materials Industry Urged to Make Big Strides </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- In a letter to a national
conference on China's building materials industry, Premier Li Peng
wrote that the sector has made great achievements since the
country adopted the policy of reforms and opening up.
</P>
<P>
Li also urges the sector to readjust and optimize the
industrial structure and develop new building materials, so as to
make historical strides.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, which opened today, Vice-Premier Wu
Bangguo also praised the progress made by the industry in the past
years.
</P>
<P>
The industry has developed at a yearly growth rate of 25
percent, faster than the average expansion of the national
economy, thanks to the efforts made by the sector's entire
workforce, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
The government has designated the building industry and the
building materials sector as two of the country's pillar
industries, but the building materials sector is still far from
meeting the needs of the growing socialist market economy, he
stressed.  
</P>
