<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Intellectual Property
Investigation Bureau of the Hong Kong Customs seized a total of
9,837 pirated video compact discs (VCDs) and 863 obscene VCDs
Monday, a spokesman for the Customs said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the value of the seizure is estimated
to be 630,000 HK dollars (about 81,290 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
