<HEADLINE> 20 Million Train Passengers in East China during Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- With the Spring Festival fast
approaching on February 7, more than 20 million people in east
China are estimated to travel by train during the holiday season
that extends from January 18 through March 8, according to the
Shanghai Railway Administration.
</P>
<P>
This indicates that there will be an average of 400,000 train
passengers per day in the area during the period, with the highest
number to reach 550,000 travelers.
</P>
<P>
