<HEADLINE> Chinese Pharmaceutical Industry's Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China's pharmaceutical sector
achieved marked successes in 1996 and made important contributions
to the national economy, Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo said today at a
national conference attended by industry representatives.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that in 1996, the pharmaceutical manufacturing sector
attained 120 billion yuan in production value, up 15 percent over
the previous year, and the domestic demand for medicine was
satisfied.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier called on those involved in the industry to
improve its efficiency, and to attempt to develop China into one
of the world's major pharmaceutical producers by relying on the
country's distinct advantages.
</P>
<P>
The pharmaceutical industry has special significance, as it is
directly related to people's health, he said.
</P>
<P>
Wu also stressed the need to promote professional ethics among
workers in the industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
