<HEADLINE> Largest US Bank Opens Branch in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Chase Manhattan Bank, the
largest financial institution in the United States, has opened a
branch in Shanghai with operations scheduled to begin in early
1997.
</P>
<P>
The branch bank will provide services for lending and risk
management to Chinese clients and transnationals investing in
China, according to its manager Peter Shay.
</P>
<P>
Chase Manhattan opened a representative office in Shanghai in
1985, and its first China branch in the north China port city of
Tianjin in 1993.
</P>
<P>
With an asset volume of more than 323 billion US dollars, Chase
has branches in more than 50 countries and regions and agent banks
in 155 countries and regions.  
