<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister on International Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen said here today that the overall
international situation is heading toward detente and
polarization, as the big countries are restructuring their
relations, and the theme of the times is peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who is also member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made the remarks
at a meeting on the world situation for leading officials of the
non-communist parties and the All China Federation for Industry
and Commerce, and for people without party affiliations.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to carry out an independent foreign policy
of peace and develop friendly and cooperative relations with
countries worldwide on the basis of the five principles of
peaceful co-existence, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Hong Kong, Qian said that the election of the
first chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region and the formation of the Preliminary Legislative Council
have created a very favorable condition for the smooth transfer of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
With the correct leadership of the CPC Central Committee and
the support of entire Chinese people, the smooth transfer of Hong
Kong and its long-term prosperity will certainly be guaranteed,
the foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
A successful implementation of the policy of "One country, two
systems" in Hong Kong will play a positive role in accomplishing
the great cause of national reunification, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 people attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
