<HEADLINE> Russia Denies Secret Rocket Talks With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- A senior Russian diplomat has
denied any secret talks between Moscow and Tehran to sell Russian
SS4 rockets to Iran, Persian daily Abrar reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sergei Tretyakov, Russian Ambassador to Iran, said "there were
no such talks ever held between Russia and Iran." He made the
remarsk while attending the opening ceremony of the two-week Tajik
peace talks which opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, Israeli newspaper Ha'aretz reported earlier that Iran
was holding talks with Russia in order to gain access to SS4
rocket technology.
</P>
<P>
Russian SS4 rocket, with a range of 2,000 kilometers, can
easily reach Israel from a launching pad in Iran, according to
the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
On December 23, Russia and Iran signed a memorandum of
understanding on the export control of weapons of mass destruction
and missile technology.
</P>
<P>
As Iran's main weapon supplier, Russia reportedly sold large
sums of advanced aircraft, tanks and submarines to Iran in the
past few years. 
