<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Hold Tea Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Urban Council and
the International Chinese Tea Club will jointly hold a tea
competition on Sunday to enhance the public's appreciation of
Chinese tea.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the organizing committee for the competition
said the final round of the Hong Kong Tea Competition will be held
in the Culture Center on Sunday with 12 finalists to compete in
producing the best brew of Tie Guanyin in front of a panel of
adjudicators formed by top tea masters from Hong Kong, the Chinese
mainland, Taiwan and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Three winners will be selected depending on their tea decoction
skill, choice of tea vessels and accessories, tea etiquette and
knowledge of Chinese tea.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said a number of related activities will be
organized on January 11 and 12, including an informative
exhibition on tea leaves and a lecture on and a demonstration of
tea culture.
</P>
<P>
The lecture is titled "the Evolution of the Theory on the Art
of Tea-Drinking in Respect of the International Development of Tea
Culture."
</P>
<P>
After the lecture, there will be an open-to-all tea ceremony
which is designed for people who are welcome to participate using
their own tea vessels and accessories such as a teapot, tea
leaves, a covered bowl, four cups, a tea jug, a tea tray, a towel
and a small thermal pot filled with hot water.  
</P>
</TEXT>
