<HEADLINE> China Selects 33 More Enterprises to List B Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Another 33 Chinese enterprises
have been given the green light to list B shares in the domestic
stock market, with the preliminary namelist recently approved by
the Securities Commission of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The selected firms were from industries of electric power,
energy resources, transportation, electronics and
telecommunications, metallurgy, machinery, petrochemicals,
textile, building materials, light industry and medicine,
according to the securities watchdog, the China Securities
Regulatory Commission (CSRC).
</P>
<P>
"Basic industries and key enterprises have received top
priority during the selection, and only firms of certain size and
with good profits were qualified," said a spokesman of the CSRC.
</P>
<P>
B shares, which are listed in the domestic stock market but
target only overseas investors, have served as an effective means
of channeling foreign capital into Chinese state enterprise, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"The B share market not only supports the technical renovations
of such enterprises, but also helps international securities
expertise to flow into the domestic securities market, which is
conducive to its standardization and maturing," he added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also urged strengthened supervision on the
current B share market in accordance with the recent State Council
rules of B share-trading, stressing that domestic investors be
strictly banned from trading of B class stocks.
</P>
<P>
So far, a total of 86 Chinese enterprises have issued and
listed B shares on the two stock exchanges in Shanghai and
Shenzhen, raising about three billion US dollars in foreign
capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
