<HEADLINE> China's Output Value of Building Materials Increases 9.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China's output value from the
building materials industry topped 260 billion yuan (about 31
billion US dollars), up 9.5 percent over 1995, according to Zhang
Renwei, director of the State Administration of Building Materials.
</P>
<P>
Speaking today at a national working conference on building
materials, Zhang said that last year, China produced 490 million
tons of cement, up 6.5 percent over 1995, and 170 million cases of
flat glass, an increase of 11.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
From January to November last year, China turned out 153
million square meters of wall and floor bricks, up 20 percent over
the corresponding period in 1995. Meanwhile, the country produced
3.91 million square meters of granite plates, up 45 percent.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that in 1996, China's production of building
materials took on following characteristics: the quality of the
products improved, with the qualification ratio arriving at 85.2
percent; the relationship between production and marketing
improved; and earnings from exports of building materials exceeded
the level of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The director said that this year, China will support the
development of large building materials enterprises, improve
industrial structure, and give priority to the development of
quality cement and quality glass urgently needed by the national
economy and for the construction of key projects.
</P>
<P>
The country will also work diligently to develop new building
materials needed for residential buildings and interior
decoration, the official added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
