<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 250 Macao residents
have applied to study in universities in china's inland areas for
master's and doctor's degrees this year, an increase of 16 people.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Macao Foundation, which assists the State
Education Commission to handle the students' recruitment affairs,
said that about half of them are applying for Zhongshan University
in Guangdong province and the Overseas Chinese University in
Fujian province.
</P>
