<HEADLINE> Hong Kong External Trade Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's total exports
increased by 4.8 percent in the first ten months of 1996 over the
same period in 1995, while imports increased by four percent.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics released today show that of the total
exports, the volume of re-exports increased by 7.6 percent, while
that of domestic exports decreased by 8.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing October 1996 with October 1995, the volume of total
exports increased by seven percent, while that of imports
increased by 7.3 percent.  
