<HEADLINE> Special Packages for ASEAN's 30th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The ASEAN Travel
Association (ASEANTA) today set up a working committee to create
special packages for the 30th anniversary of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) this year.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN's 30th anniversary has been considered an important
event for the region's tourism industry with plans afoot to sell
the seven member countries as "must" destinations for tourists.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN members are Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
