<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970107.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Outlines New Poverty Eradication Plan  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- China is to redouble its efforts
to wipe out poverty in its rural areas in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
According to a decision of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and the State Council, the
fulfillment of a national key task plan to help millions of poor
people escape poverty is a strategic goal.
</P>
<P>
When a poverty-relief plan was first drawn up in 1993, there
were 80 million people living in poverty throughout the
country. By the end of last year, the figure had fallen to 65
million.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and the State Council have vowed to
ensure that all poverty-ridden people in the country's rural areas
have enough to eat and wear by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The 7,000-character document, entitled "Decision of the CPC
Central Committee and the State Council on Solving the Problem of
Having Enough to Eat and Wear for Poor People in Rural Areas As
Soon As Possible," was released today.
</P>
<P>
The document follows an important meeting held last October on
the issue of eliminating poverty held by the CPC and the State
Council last October.
</P>
<P>
"It is of great significance to realize this goal, but the time
is urgent and the task is very arduous," says the document.
</P>
<P>
The decision calls on all Party members, especially leading
officials at various levels, to increase their awareness of
poverty elimination, and unify their way of thinking, be firmer
with their decisions, and take more effective measures to ensure
the completion of the great historical task as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to complete the key task of poverty eradication
in an unswerving way, adds the document.
</P>
<P>
Since 1979, and especially since mid-1980s when China started
to carry out a great number of large-scale aid-to-the-poor
programs in an organized, planned way, the number of the country's
poor people has fallen sharply, from 250 million in 1978 to 65
million in 1996.
</P>
<P>
This has also brought down the proportion of poor people from a
previous 26 percent to the present 5.4 percent of the population.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, conditions for production and living, as well
as basic facilities have improved enormously in poverty-hit
areas, coupled with fresh progress in cultural, educational and
public health causes.
</P>
<P>
The achievement has effectively advanced the development of the
national economy and social stability, fully demonstrating the
advantages of China's socialist system, the decision notes.
</P>
<P>
The decision has also listed the basic principles, task and
requirements for the key task of tackling of poverty eradication.
</P>
<P>
According to the decision, China will continue to consider
solving the problem of having enough to eat and wear for poor
people in rural areas as a primary task, and continue the campaign
of helping the poor by starting up new economic development
projects.
</P>
<P>
Plantations, breeding and processing industries based on farm
and sideline products in respective localities, which are
conducive to generating more profits and helping more poor people
become prosperous quickly, will remain the priority of
aid-to-the-poor work.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it is also necessary to do a good job of applying
science and education to aid-to-the-poor work, and to making a
success of family planning programs in poverty-hit areas, and give
guidance suited to local conditions.
</P>
<P>
The document also emphasizes the importance of implementing
aid-to-the-poor work on a household basis, carrying forward the
spirit of self-reliance and working hard, and mobilizing all
sectors of the society to participate in help-the-poor work.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970107.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Outlines Poverty Eradication Plan  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Outlining major measures to be taken in coming years, the
decision explains that the central government will allocate an
additional 1.5 billion yuan to help economic development in
poverty-stricken areas in each of the next few years starting from
this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, government loans to help the poor will be
increased by three billion yuan annually.
</P>
<P>
More large projects, such as irrigation schemes, infrastructure
work and transport facilities, will be built in areas where
people live in compact communities.
</P>
<P>
Governments at all levels should keep a tight control on funds
to be used in boosting economic development of poor areas.
</P>
<P>
Households which have difficulty in getting adequate food and
clothing will be exempted from state fixed quotas on grain
purchasing, agricultural taxes and taxes levied on special farm
products.
</P>
<P>
Industrial enterprises built in poor areas by well-developed
provinces and cities, or by the poor areas themselves, will be
exempted from the income tax in the first three years of operation.
</P>
<P>
The amount of special funds for the construction and
maintenance of resettlement villages at areas to be flooded for
the sake of large water control projects will be raised.
</P>
<P>
Economically-developed coastal areas, and municipalities
directly under the central government are urged to forge
sister-ties with poverty-stricken areas in central and western
parts of the country, and provide their counterparts with funds,
technology, information and technical personnel.
</P>
<P>
Central government departments will organize training courses
for leading officials and managerial personnel in poor areas.
</P>
<P>
More efforts will be made to promote exchanges and cooperation
with international and non-governmental organizations to win their
support and economic assistance for poverty-elimination.
</P>
<P>
In conclusion, the document states that Party committees and
governments at all levels must conscientiously implement policies
formulated by the Party Central Committee and the State Council on
poverty eradication, and work in a down-to-earth manner to
accomplish what will be a great historical task.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
