<HEADLINE> Magic Johnson Arrives for Charity Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, Janaury 7 (Xinhua) -- Former NBA star Magic Johnson
arrived here Tuesday though the Indonesia's health minister said
the public had to be warned that Johnson could spread the virus
that causes AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Johnson and his all-star team is scheduled to play games
Wednesday and Thursday to raise money for AIDS campaigns in
Indonesia, where the World Health Organization says some 50,000
people are infected with the virus, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Suyudi Monday denied a claim that Johnson was
rejected an Indonesian visa in February 1995 and said the
government welcomed Johnson's visit this week.
</P>
<P>
"But the society should get information on the spread of HIV so
that this HIV-positive athlete will not spread the disease,"
Suyudi, who uses one name, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, 38, is a three-time NBA MVP who led the Lakers to five
league titils during the 1980s. 
</P>
