<HEADLINE> Thai Charter Drafting Assembly Chairman Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Former Thai parliament speaker
Ukrit Mongkolnavin today was elected as chairman of the country's
Constitution Drafting Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Ukrit won the post with 65 votes in favor and 30 against when
the 99-member newly-established panel held its first meeting
today.
</P>
<P>
The 99 members of the assembly were elected on December 26 last
year at a joint meeting of the House of Representatives and the
Senate, and they will write the kingdom's 16th version of the
constitution as part of political reform in the kingdom.
</P>
<P>
The body is expected to prepare a draft constitution for
parliamentary approval within 240 days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
