<HEADLINE> PLA Supports Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army
(PLA), China's armed forces, has taken an active attitude towards
the country's economic construction, by offering more than 100
million labor days in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
According to the PLA General Political Department, PLA officers
and men have taken part in more than 30,000 state key projects and
other public-spirited items, and helped nearly two million poor
families relieve poverty and become better off.
</P>
<P>
China's key projects, including the Three Gorges Dam,
Beijing-Kowloon Railway, A south-to-north Water Diversion and an
optical cable line, have all received full support from the army.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, the army has mobilized some 200,000
soldiers to lay 20,000 kilometers of telecommunications cable
lines between Beijing and Lanzhou, Guangzhou, Xi'an, and between
Xi'an and Urumqi. The cables have covered 20 provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities, and accounted for one-third of the key
projects of the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese soldiers have also taken part in various
poverty-relief projects in the country's underdeveloped regions
and helped set up 30,000 poverty relief centers.
</P>
<P>
By providing economic information and training personnel, the
army has helped two million poor families relieve poverty and
become better off.
</P>
<P>
The army helped set up 45,000 township enterprises and
household-based farms in underdeveloped areas, and set up more
than 20,000 economic communities to boost local economies.
</P>
<P>
Army academies, research institutes and information agencies
have also turned their findings to civil purposes, with the
economic rewards described as satisfactory.
</P>
<P>
Military industries can manufacture over 15,000 kinds of
civil-use products, and 2,500 items of national defence
technologies have been turned over to civil use, generating 10
billion yuan in annual output value.
</P>
<P>
And the production of motorcycles and color television sets by
military companies has respectively accounted for 60 and 30
percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
The application of nuclear technology in agriculture has added
at least one billion kilograms of grain annually.
</P>
<P>
The army also participated in nearly 9,000 public-spirited
projects which were directly in the interests of the people.
</P>
<P>
Army units stationed in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region
have helped local residents drill over 200 wells and lay more than
10,000 meters of water pipes, helping local farmers and herdsmen
to solve water supply problems.  
</P>
</TEXT>
