<HEADLINE> Tianjin Witnesses Rapid Growth of Firms With Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-financed enterprises in
north China's port city of Tianjin contributed 40 percent to the
city's total industrial output value in 1996, according to latest
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Municipal Commission of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation show that the city has more than 3,200
foreign-funded enterprises, whose combined output value amounted
to 50.7 billion yuan in the first three quarters of last year, up
44.2 percent over the same period in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The firms have enjoyed a good economic return, with profits
totaling 4.89 billion yuan in the first nine months of 1996, an
increase of 33.3 percent over the same period in 1995, statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of the city's investment environment, the
old industrial base has attracted an overseas investment adding up
to 5.7 billion US dollars over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
According to analysts, the number of international enterprise
groups and consortiums that have investments in Tianjin amounts to
189, with the bulk of their investments in industrial projects.
</P>
<P>
The city's comparatively advanced infrastructure, sufficient
technical personnel, and low salary levels, all contributed to the
rapid growth of the enterprises, analysts said.  
</P>
