<HEADLINE> More New Biomedicines Produced in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Newly-invented products have
proved a tonic for the pillar industry of biomedicine in Shanghai,
with profits from the medicines making up 79 percent of the
industry's total last year.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the output value of the new products accounted for 21
percent of the total output value of the biomedicine industry, up
14 percent from three years ago.
</P>
<P>
The output value of the industry, which was estimated at 12.5
billion yuan (about 1.5 billion US dollars) last year, increased
by 25 percent, compared with the figure of 1995.
</P>
<P>
During the past three years, 152 types of biomedicines have
been invented and 122 are on the market. Among the 122, 16 have
been recognized by the Ministry of Public Health as medicines
developed using the most advanced techniques.
</P>
<P>
The inventions include some gene engineering medicines, such as
streptokinase (SK), used for cardiovascular disease, a growth
hormone for children, interleukin-2 for curbing the growth of
tumors, and the hepatitis-c vaccine.
</P>
<P>
The city has set its goal for the total output value of the
industry by the year 2000 at 30 billion yuan (about 3.6 billion US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
During the last four years of the century, it will develop new
products for health care, pesticide and three other fields,
focusing on the medicine for cardiovascular diseases,
anti-infection, tumor treatment, sterility-improvement and
senility-related diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
