<HEADLINE> 500-Ton Floating Glass Production Line Built in Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUOYANG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A line to produce 500 tons of
floating glass a day has been built at a joint-venture company in
Qingdao involving Hong Kong funding.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the production line, valued at 600 million
yuan, began in May 1995 in Qingdao Taiyang Glass Industrial
Co. Ltd., which is a joint effort involving the Luoyang Floating
Glass Company in central China's Henan Province, a company in
northwest Shaanxi Province, and two companies from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The line is expected to manufacture 2.62 million crates of
floating glass a year.
</P>
<P>
In addition to imported equipment and technology, the joint
venture introduced the Luoyang company's key floating
glass-producing techniques, which are among the top in the world,
helping it to lead the country in technology and automation in
glass production.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the production line in Qingdao, the Luoyang
company has so far cooperated with other companies to build two
more such ventures, bringing its total floating glass production
lines to six.
</P>
<P>
The Luoyang company now contributes one-fifth of the country's
total floating glass output. 
</P>
