dozen heavily armed Peruvian rebels stormed the Japanese
ambassador's residence in Lima during a party in honor of Japanese
Emperor Akihito.
</P>
<P>
While most of the captives were set free under international
rescue efforts, there are still 74 hostages remaining in the
rebels' hands, including Japanese ambassador to Peru and Peruvian
foreign minister. 
