<HEADLINE> Buddhist Museum Established in Suzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, January 7 (Xinhua) -- A Buddhist museum will soon open
to the public in Suzhou, a famous tourist resort in east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The museum is located in the former Baoguo Temple and covers an
area of 1,200 square meters. It has a main building, a house for
Buddhist sutras and affiliated houses.
</P>
<P>
The museum's display will include articles, written material
and pictures on historical temples, figures and sutras of Buddha,
details on the lives of renowned monks, instruments used in a
Buddhist mass, and other items related to Buddhist ceremonies.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou has a history of 1,700 years of Buddhism worship which
has played an important part in local culture.
</P>
<P>
The city has more than ten temples which each have a history of
over 1,000 years.
</P>
<P>
The local temples are noted for their classic appearance,
delicate Buddhist sculptures, carvings, poems and proses in honor
of Buddha. 
</P>
