<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has called on all Sri Lankans to participate actively
in the task of nation building to enable the country to march into
the 21st century as a prosperous, united and peaceful nation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting of Muslim Ladies College here Sunday
evening, she said that the government was making every effort to
restore harmony among different communities socially,
politically, constitutionally, culturally and educationally,
according to official sources here today.
