Children of different communities will be given an opportunity
to learn each other's native languages under the proposed
educational reforms, she said.
</P>
<P>
She noted that the basic problem affecting the country was that
one ethnic group did not know the language spoken by the other.
</P>
<P>
Sinhalese Tamils and Muslims and several other communities had
been living in the country for centuries in harmony participating
in each other's social and cultural functions, but somewhere down
the line many things happened in the political and social spheres
to divide the masses, the president pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"This had led to the terrible consequences that we experienced
today," the president said, adding that the diversity of cultural
traditions of various communities had contributed to the richness
of the country's cultural legacy.  
