<HEADLINE> Thailand Axes Airline, Military Spending Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh has instructed Thai Airways International (Thai) and
the military to shelve some of their major purchase plans in order
to cut the current account deficit.
</P>
