<HEADLINE> Thai Baht Drops to Record Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Thai baht fell five satang
further on Monday to 25.65 against the US dollar from last Friday,
reaching a four-year low.
</P>
<P>
The Thai central bank declined to intervene despite the
depreciation of the baht, saying it is normal for the baht to
weaken as the US dollar appreciated on the world market.
</P>
<P>
The US dollar reportedly closed at 116.98 yen on Monday in
Tokyo market against 115.70 yen last Friday. Thai newspapers
quoted dealers as saying that the baht would depreciate one satang
if the dollar appreciates by every 0.30 yen.
</P>
<P>
The reaction to whether the depreciation of the baht would boost
Thai exports remained mixed, but dealers and central bank
officials said it would do little to spur Thai exports. 
</P>
