<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Government, MILF to Open Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The peace panels of the
Philippine government and the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF)
will hold the first meeting of their technical working committees
in Maguindanao province, Central Mindanao, today to map out
details of their succeeding talks.
</P>
<P>
Panel officials said the meeting, hosted by the Maguindanao
provincial government, will begin at 10 a.m. with simple
ceremonies at the Da'wa Center in Baragnay Simuay, Sultan Kudarat
town.
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to attend the meeting are members and officials of
the committees on ceasefire and on peace talks' ground rules of
both the government and MILF peace panels.
</P>
<P>
Brig. Gen. Joselin Nazareno, the Army's 4th Infantry Division
chief, and Joey Lazaga of the Office of the Press Secretary will
head the government ceasefire committee and ground rules committee
respectively. Their MILF counterparts are lawyer Lanang Ali and
Ustaz Moner Bajunaid.
</P>
<P>
Ghazzali Jaafar, MILF vice chairman for political affairs, said
the rebel group will submit in today's meeting its proposals that
would specify the details of a government-MILF ceasefire
agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
