<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Unlicensed Businessmen Imprisoned in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Two unlicensed video business
operators in Myanmar have been sentenced to 10 years' imprisonment
respectively by a local township court, The New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The two, who are a man and a woman, were operating video
business without licenses copying and distributing with illegally
imported electronic appliances, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The two were sentenced last Friday with rigorous labor under
Myanmar's Television and Video Law which was enacted last July,
and the Export and Import Supervision Act, the report added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
