<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Cancels Activities Due to Cold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
has canceled activities scheduled for the next few days due to a
"bad cold" and mild fever he is suffering, the presidential press
office said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Presidential press secretary Sergei Yastrzhembsky said
Yeltsin's cold had nothing to do with the heart by-pass operation
which the president undertook on November 5, but might be
infected by the flu spreading in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Yastrzhembsky also said Yeltsin called a meeting on Monday in
the Kremlin to discuss Russia's policy towards the eastward
expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, which was attended by Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin, Presidential Office Director Anatoly Chubais and
Security Council Secretary Ivan Rybkin, Yeltsin reiterated
Russia's opposition to NATO's expansion and gave detailed orders
on steps that Russia would take, Yastrzhembsky said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
