<HEADLINE> Russia's Nuclear Energy Export Rises in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia's nuclear energy export
reached 2.2 billion U.S. dollars in 1996, 150-200 million dollars
higher than in 1995, a ranking official said today.
</P>
<P>
Atomic Energy Minister Viktor Mikhailov said that the
ministry's import last year was 100 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
His ministry has carried out or is studying the plans on the
building of nuclear power plants in Iran, China, India and Cuba.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia and China will sign a contract this year on
the construction of a nuclear power plant in Lianyungang, China.
After the completion, he said, Russia's nuclear export to China
will rise to 800 million dollars from 250 million dollars in
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
