<HEADLINE> Brazil to Carry Out Economic Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government will
restructure 15 sectors of its economy to make them more
competitive on international market, the Ministry of Industry,
Commerce and Tourism said today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, incentives including bank loans will also be given
to these sectors, such as capital goods, electronics, automobile,
naval construction, computer and civil construction.
</P>
<P>
The government hopes that these measures will help create more
jobs and increase exports, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
