<HEADLINE> Floods, Snowstorms Hit Georgia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Floods and snowstorms have hit
the Republic of Georgia in recent days, killing three people and
causing enormous property losses.
</P>
<P>
In a speech delivered Monday, Georgian President Eduard
Shevardnadze said that the country has lost about 19.5 million
U.S. dollars in damage in the recent floods and snowstorms.
</P>
<P>
From late December to early January this year, one flood after
another ravaged Georgia, paralyzing the water system and traffic
in many parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, about 50 highway bridges and thousands
of buildings and hectares of farmland were destroyed in the
floods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
