<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovakia's Foreign Reserve Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia's foreign reserve
reached 5.8 billion dollars at the end of last year, a record high
since the country became independent in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Of the total which was 15 percent higher than a year ago, 3.4
billion dollars were held by the state bank and 2.3 billion
dollars by the commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
A state bank spokesman attributed the foreign reserve increase
to the continuous economic recovery, steadier development speed,
lower inflation rate and increased foreign investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
