<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian-Argentine Trade Increases in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Argentina and
Brazil reached 12 billion U.S. dollars in 1996, or 2.4 billion
dollars more than the 1995 total, official figures showed.
</P>
<P>
Argentina's embassy in Brasilia said today that Brazil exported
5.5 billion dollars worth of goods to Argentina last year and its
imports from the country stood at 6.5 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries is expected to increase to 14
billion dollars in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Argentine embassy sources said that joint investments by the
two countries in different economic sectors have registered
enormous and dynamic gains in the past few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
