<HEADLINE> Hardaway Returns to Orlando </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, Janaury 6 (Xinhua) -- The Olympic champion "Dream
Team" guard Anfernee Hardaway participated workouts Monday on the
Orlando Magic's arena and should return to the NBA league for
Tuesday's game.
</P>
<P>
Hardaway has missed 23 of 28 games this season for the Magic
and 11 games since December 18 due to tendinitis, reports said.
</P>
<P>
At 11-17, the Magic is a far cry from the squad that reached
the 1995 NBA Final.
</P>
<P>
Orlando have slid to a 7-16 record without Hardaway, losing
nine of 11 games during his latest absence. He underwent
arthroscopic surgery on his left knee on November 17 to repair
torn cartilage.
</P>
<P>
Hardaway has averaged 20.2 points, 5.8 assists and 5.8 rebounds
a game for Orlando, which waived Kenny Smith to make room for
Hardaway on the active roster. Ednitem

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
