<HEADLINE> Kenyans 1-2-3 in Milan Cross Country Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Double world cross country champion
Paul Tergat led fellow Kenyans to a 1-2-3 finish in the Campaccio
race in Milan on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Tergat, beaten here in 1995 in 1996, clocked 36 minutes and 15
seconds over the 12 kilometers course, beating David Chelule by
one second and Paul Koech two.
</P>
<P>
Terget took the 10,000 meters silver medal in the Atlanta
Olympic Games last summer.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan women were denied a clean sweep as Kutre Dulecha of
Ethiopia nipped Rose Kosgei to win the 6 kilometers race.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian clocked 21:38 to win by two seconds. 
</P>
