<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles to Miss Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles would not be able
to defend her title of the upcoming Australian Open in Melbourne
due to a broken finger.
</P>
<P>
Reports said Seles broke her right ring finger in early
December while warming up for an exhibition tournament. X-rays
revealed the finger is broken in two places, the knuckle and
finger tip.
</P>
<P>
"I want so much to return to Australia, where I have so many
happy memories," Seles said in a statement released Monday. "All I
can do is look forward to 1998 with great anticipation."
</P>
<P>
The world number four has won four Australian Open titles and
is unbeaten in her career in Australia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
