<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Regains Lead for Mitsubishi in Dakar Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Kenjiro Shinozuka regained
the Dakar-Agades-Dakar rally lead for Mitsubishi on Monday when he
won the 552-km third stage from Kayes to Nara in Mali.
</P>
<P>
Shinozuka overtook previous overall leader Jean-Louis Schlesser
midway in the stage and drove home first.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese now leads Schlesser by two minutes 41 seconds.
Mitsubishi drivers Jean-Pierre Fontenay and Saby finished third
and fourth, 4:12 and 4:33 behind respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the motorcycle section, the four times winner Stephane
Peterhansel won his third successive stage in a Yamaha.
</P>
<P>
But the Frenchman had to hold off a tough challenge from
Spain's Jordi Arcarons, who finished just behind on his KTM.
</P>
</TEXT>
